hello I'm Samira an escalation
specialist here at the AWS office in
Cape Town today I'm going to show you
how to get help with your AWS Services

showing you how to search for Content
using the various documentation

started there are several resources
available to get help with your AWS
Services account or billing queries we
will start by looking at AWS
repost open the AWS repost
website here you can search for Content
that's related to your question if you
don't find what you're looking for you
can ask a new question and other a users
or AWS Engineers might be able to help
you AWS
documentation open the AWS documentation
website here you can find documentation
for the specific AWS service that you're
using including troubleshooting guides
and tutorials for common use
cases AWS prescriptive guidance open the
AWS prescriptive guidance
website here you can search for res
sources on how to migrate to AWS and how
to optimize or modernize your Cloud
operations AWS support all AWS customers
can contact AWS support for account and
billing queries as well as to request
service quota
increases for an account or billing
related question after logging into your
AWS account open the AWS Support Center
ENT choose create
case select account and
billing select the relevant
service and select the relevant
category click on Next
Step full in the subject field as well
as the description field click Next
Step you now have two options available
you can either refer to the self-help
options on the screen alternatively you
can contact us directly select your
preference for contact options choose
submit to request a service quota
increase select create
case click on looking for service quoter
increases select service quoters
dashboard click on AWS
services enter the service that you
would like to request the service quoter
increase for select the resource that
you would like the service quoter
increase for click on request increase
at account level verify that the
information is correct click on
request if you need oneon-one technical
support you must upgrade your support
plan after logging in open the AWS
Support
Center choose View support
plans click on select a support
plan select the desired support plan
accept and
agree now you know how to get help with
your AWS Services account or
billing thanks for watching and happy
cloud computing from all of us here at
AWS
